<h1 class="docs-header">Forms</h1>

<p>HTML forms are probably the most daunting part of front-end development to markup and style. BaseWeb's goal is to give you the tools to make forms easy to build and flexible.</p>

<hr class="docs-hr">

<section class="sub-section sub-section-classes">

<h1 class="docs-header">Form Structure</h1>

<p>Along with all standard form elements, BaseWeb provides you with <code>.form-group</code>, <code>.input-group</code> and <code>.action-group</code> classes to use for structuring a form layout.</p>

<pre class="language-markup"><code>
&lt;form&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;Input Group&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;input-group&quot;&gt;
      ...
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;Inline Input Group&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;input-group inline-group&quot;&gt;
      ...
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;action-group&quot;&gt;
    ...
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
</code></pre>

<div class="demo">
  <form>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>Example Label</label>
      <div class="input-group">
        <input class="input" type="text" placeholder="Example text input..." required>
        <select class="input">
          <option>Option 1</option>
          <option>Option 2</option>
          <option>Option 3</option>
        </select>
        <select class="input" multiple>
          <option>Option 1</option>
          <option>Option 2</option>
          <option>Option 3</option>
        </select>
        <textarea class="input" rows="4"></textarea>
      </div>
      
      <label>Example Label</label>
      <div class="input-group inline-group">
        <label class="choice"><input type="checkbox"> Choice checkbox</label>
        <label class="choice"><input type="radio"> Choice radio</label>
      </div>
    </div>
      
    <div class="action-group">
      <button class="btn btn-primary">Button</button>
      <button class="btn btn-default">Button</button>
    </div>
      
  </form>
</div>

