        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  
  </li>
  
  <li>
    
    <h2 class="docs-header">Form Grids</h2>
    <p>For more complex form layouts, you also have BaseWeb's default grid system to create rows and columns.</p>
    
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>
&lt;form&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;Grid Example&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col col-4&quot;&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col col-4&quot;&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col col-4&quot;&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
    </code></pre>
    
    <div class="demo">
      <form>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label>Grid Example</label>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col col-4">
              <input class="input" type="text" placeholder="Example">
            </div>
            <div class="col col-4">
              <select class="input">
                <option>Option 1</option>
                <option>Option 2</option>
                <option>Option 3</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="col col-4">
              <label class="choice"><input type="checkbox" checked> Choice</label>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  
  </li>

</ul>

